1)History of Pardus Operating System
First studies started in 2003 by TUBITAK. Due to these exploration, in the late 2003,
it was decided to create an operating system distribution based on Linux, which is open source.The Pardus Project started at the beginning of 2004 with a team working within Tübitak.Pardus developed stabled with turkey state . Nowadays, the Turkey state still use Pardus operating system due to security.Pardus developed with many programming languages, that's why It's easy to use and cheaper.


2)Which Memory Management does The Pardus OS Use
Pardus OS makes use of GNU/Linux Memory Management. It is the system of controlling and dealing with pc memory, assigning portions referred to as blocks to diverse walking applications to optimize the complete system performance.

3)Which File System does The Pardus OS Use?
It makes use of GNU/Linux File System. A document device reads and writes the sectors at the storage drive. The document device manages the folder/listing shape and offers an index to the files. In this device the complete document-listing hierarchy inclusive of hardware is a document connected to a root.

4)Usage fields and purpose
Fields:
Turkish Armed Forces
Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Turkey) 
Ministry of National Defence (Turkey) 
Social Security Institution  
Purpose:
•	Turkey used Pardus because it’s a completely Turkish operating system.
•	Hard to Hack\Durable security

•	Easy to use

•	For schools, it’s used in ETAP project which is a project of letting teachers and students to use a interactive board.

